reviews.text: Bought tickets at the self service booth.....the wrong tickets.....spoke to the lady who was sorting the machines, even though she was abit abrupt at times, she did help me get a refund and issue me the correct tickets , even though the office was closed....she did let me know it was above and beyond standard practice but I did appreciate it!
Train go via Chiswick and take ages to go Waterloo compare to Woking route.
An attractive railway station on the Chertsey Branch. Steam trains pass through fairly regularly.

I'm 15 and I get the train to college 3 times a week. The woman i bought the tickets from explained that even though I'm 15 I can no longer buy child tickets because "if I'm old enough to go to college I'm old enough to pay for an adult ticket" which makes no sense whatsoever and seeing as tho I'm legally allowed to buy a child ticket for another year. Also, you can now start college from the age of 14.
